These are the 10 biggest stock winners Monday as the market rebounds from coronavirus rout

U.S. stocks came roaring back Monday, breaking a seven-day losing streak after the S&P 500 Index hit its last closing record Feb. 19.

Investors jumped on buying opportunities. The benchmark S&P 500 SPX, +1.19%  shot up 4.6%, while the Dow Jones Industrial Average DJIA, +0.52%  did even better, adding 1,294 points (or 5.1%) to close at 26,703.32. The Nasdaq Composite Index COMP, +1.64%  climbed 4.5%.

